  "notes": "Tahitian (Reo Tahiti), Eastern Polynesian language of French Polynesia. Very small inventory: nine consonants /p t m n f v h r ʔ/ and five vowel qualities, each with a phonemic long counterpart written with a macron (tārava). The glottal stop (ʼeta) is a full consonant and is written with an apostrophe — the straight, curly and modifier-letter forms are all accepted as graphemes here. /r/ is an alveolar trill, also heard as a flap.",
